%header
  .container
    %h1 Minimal CSS Framework for semantic HTML
    %p
      Elegant styles for all natives HTML elements without
      %code .classes
      and dark mode automatically enabled.
    %p
      %a.secondary{"aria-label" => "Documentation", :href => "docs/", :role => "button"} Get started
      %a.contrast.outline{"aria-label" => "Download", :href => "https://github.com/picocss/pico/archive/refs/heads/master.zip", :role => "button"} Download
    %p
      %code
        %small Less than 10 kB minified and gzipped
%main
  %section#demo{"aria-label" => "Demo"}
    .container
      %article{"aria-label" => "Rendered demo", "data-theme" => "light"}
        #render
          %form{"aria-busy" => "true"}
        %pre
          %code#code
  %section#principles
    .container
      %hgroup
        %h2 Letâ€™s keep the webdesign graceful and simple!
        %h3 With just the right amount of everything, Pico is great starting point for a clean and lightweight design system.
      .grid
        %div
          %h4 Class-light and semantic
          %p We use simple native HTML tags as much as possible. Less than 10 .classes are used in Pico.
        %div
          %h4 Great styles with just CSS
          %p No dependencies, package manager, external files, or JavaScript.
        %div
          %h4 Responsive everything
          %p Elegant and consistent adaptive spacings and typography on all devices.
        %div
          %h4 Light or Dark mode
          %p Shipped with two beautiful color themes, automatically enabled according to the user preference.
  %section#examples{"data-theme" => "light"}
    .container
      %hgroup
        %h2 Examples
        %h3 Minimalist templates to discover Pico in action.
      .grid
        %div
          %a{:href => "examples/preview/"}
            %small Preview
            .example.preview
              .desktop
              .mobile
          %p
            %small A starter example with all elements and components used in Pico
        %div
          %a{:href => "examples/classless/"}
            %small Class-less
            .example.classless
              .desktop
              .mobile
          %p
            %small
              Just a pure semantic HTML markup, without
              %code .classes
        %div
          %a{:href => "examples/basic-template/"}
            %small Basic template
            .example.basic-template
              .desktop
              .mobile
          %p
            %small A basic custom template for Pico using only CSS custom properties (variables)
        %div
          %a{:href => "examples/company/"}
            %small Company
            .example.company
              .desktop
              .mobile
          %p
            %small A classic company or blog layout with a sidebar
        %div
          %a{:href => "examples/google-amp/"}
            %small Google Amp
            .example.google-amp
              .desktop
              .mobile
          %p
            %small A simple layout for Google Amp, with inlined CSS
        %div
          %a{:href => "examples/sign-in/"}
            %small Sign in
            .example.sign-in
              .desktop
              .mobile
          %p
            %small A minimalist layout for Login pages
  %section#why
    .container
      %hgroup
        %h2 More Code, More Problems
        %h3 A great design should be minimal, fast and maintainable.
      %ul.check
        %li
          Most popular CSS frameworks are bulky, overkill and hard to customize without
          %em hyper-overriding
          styles.
        %li Huge stackings of wrappers and CSS classes are unnecessary for semantics elements.
        %li Large and complex CSS file increase memory usage and cause longer style calculations.
        %li Basics HTML elements should not require packaging large amount of dependencies.
      %div{"data-theme" => "invalid"}
        %pre
          %code
            \<
            %b form
            = succeed "=" do
              %i class
            = succeed ">" do
              %u "form form-modifier margin padding align"
            %b div
            = succeed "=" do
              %i class
            = succeed ">" do
              %u "input-wrapper input-wrapper-modifier margin padding"
            %b input
            = succeed "=" do
              %i type
            %u "text"
            = succeed "=" do
              %i class
            = succeed ">" do
              %u "input input-type-modifier input-style-modifier input-size-modifier"
            = succeed ">" do
              %b div
            %b button
            = succeed "=" do
              %i type
            = succeed "\"" do
              %u "submit
            = succeed "=" do
              %i class
            = succeed ">" do
              %u "button button-style-modifier button-size-modifier action-trigger margin padding"
            = succeed ">" do
              %b button
            = succeed ">" do
              %b form
      %div{"data-theme" => "valid"}
        %pre
          %code
            \<
            %b> form
            \>
            \<
            %b input
            = succeed "=" do
              %i type
            = succeed ">" do
              %u "text"
            %b button
            = succeed "=" do
              %i type
            = succeed ">Action</" do
              %u "submit"
            = succeed ">" do
              %b button
            = succeed ">" do
              %b form
